column6: LPRCA worked with MNRF to re-introduce a self-sustaining population of brook trout to Gilvesy Creek, tributary of Little Otter Creek using a local stock.
column7: Gilvesy Creek historically had a resident brook trout population that had been extirpated. To re-introduce a self-sustaining population using a local stock, 15 juvenile and 10 adult resident brook trout were captured and relocated from Cranberry Creek Municipal drain to Gilvesy Creek, a tributary of Little Otter Creek, downstream of the YU Ranch in Elgin County. The population in Cranberry Creek was not detrimentally impacted; the CPUE of brook trout captured through electrofishing (27 trout in 22.5 minutes) indicated a healthy population exists. The relocation activity involved LPRCA, MNRF, NLSC and Bryan Gilvesy (landowner).
